model.quickbooks_source.stg_quickbooks__.description: Table containing all vendor records. A vendor is the seller from whom your company purchases any service or product.

account_number.name: account_number
account_number.description: Name or number of the account associated with this vendor.

billing_address_id.name: billing_address_id
billing_address_id.description: Address reference for the billing address of the vendor.

is_active.name: is_active
is_active.description: Boolean indicating whether the vendor is active.

balance.name: balance
balance.description: Specifies the open balance amount or the amount unpaid by the customer.

company_name.name: company_name
company_name.description: The name of the company associated with the person or organization.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: Timestamp of the date when the vendor was created.

currency_id.name: currency_id
currency_id.description: Reference to the currency in which all amounts associated with this vendor are expressed.

display_name.name: display_name
display_name.description: The name of the vendor as displayed. Must be unique across all Vendor, Customer, and Employee objects.

web_url.name: web_url
web_url.description: Website url associated with the vendor.

is_vendor_1099.name: is_vendor_1099
is_vendor_1099.description: Boolean indicating whether this vendor is an independent contractor; someone who is given a 1099-MISC form at the end of the year.

balance.name: balance

model.quickbooks_source.stg_quickbooks__.description: Table containing payment transactions bills that the business owner receives from a vendor for goods or services purchased from the vendor.

bill_payment_id.name: bill_payment_id
bill_payment_id.description: Unique identifier of the bill payment.

check_bank_account_id.name: check_bank_account_id
check_bank_account_id.description: Account id of the account which the bill payment is credited. Only applicable if bill payment `pay_type` is of type check.

check_print_status.name: check_print_status
check_print_status.description: Status of the check which was used as payment for the bill. Only applicable if bill payment `pay_type` is of type Check.

credit_card_account_id.name: credit_card_account_id
credit_card_account_id.description: Account id of the account which the bill is credited. Only applicable if bill payment `pay_type` is of type CreditCard.

exchange_rate.name: exchange_rate
exchange_rate.description: The number of home currency units it takes to equal one unit of currency specified by CurrencyRef. Applicable if multicurrency is enabled for the company.

currency_id.name: currency_id
currency_id.description: Reference to the currency in which all amounts on the associated transaction are expressed.

department_id.name: department_id
department_id.description: Reference to a Department object specifying the location of the transaction.

pay_type.name: pay_type
pay_type.description: The payment type. Valid values include Check, CreditCard

total_amount.name: total_amount
total_amount.description: Indicates the total amount associated with this payment. This includes the total of all the payments from the payment line details.

transaction_date.name: transaction_date
transaction_date.description: Timestamp of the day the transaction took place.

vendor_id.name: vendor_id
vendor_id.description: Reference to the vendor for this transaction.

_fivetran_deleted.name: _fivetran_deleted
_fivetran_deleted.description: Boolean created by Fivetran to indicate whether the record has been deleted.

model.quickbooks_source.stg_quickbooks__.description: Table containing components of a Chart Of Accounts and is part of a ledger. It is used to record a total monetary amount allocated against a specific use. Accounts are one of five basic types: asset, liability, revenue (income), expenses, or equity.

account_number.name: account_number
account_number.description: User-defined account number intended to identify the account within the Chart of Accounts.

is_sub_account.name: is_sub_account
is_sub_account.description: Specifies whether this object represents a parent (false) or a sub_account (true).

parent_account_id.name: parent_account_id
parent_account_id.description: User entered description for the account.

name.name: name
name.description: User recognizable name for the Account.

account_type.name: account_type
account_type.description: A detailed account classification that specifies the use of this account. The type is based on the Classification.

is_active.name: is_active
is_active.description: Boolean indicating whether an account is currently active.

account_sub_type.name: account_sub_type
account_sub_type.description: The account sub-type classification and is based on the AccountType value.

classification.name: classification
classification.description: The classification of an account. Not supported for non-posting accounts. Valid values include Asset, Equity, Expense, Liability, Revenue.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: Timestamp of the date the account was created.

currency_id.name: currency_id
currency_id.description: Reference to the currency which the account records the balance in.

description.name: description
description.description: Description of the account.

balance.name: balance
balance.description: Specifies the balance amount for the current Account.

balance_with_sub_accounts.name: balance_with_sub_accounts
balance_with_sub_accounts.description: Specifies the balance amount for the current Account sub accounts.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: Timestamp of the date which the account was last updated.

receivable_account_id.description: Identifies the account for obtaining a receivable from this payment.

deposit_to_account_id.description: Identifies the account to be used for this payment.

customer_id.name: customer_id
customer_id.description: Reference to a customer or job.

total_amount.description: Indicates the total credit amount, determined by taking the total of all all lines of the transaction.

exchange_rate.name: exchange_rate
exchange_rate.description: The number of home currency units it takes to equal one unit of currency specified by currency_id.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: Timestamp of the date the vendor credit was created.

payable_account_id.name: payable_account_id
payable_account_id.description: Specifies to which AP account the bill is credited.

private_note.name: private_note

transaction_date.name: transaction_date
transaction_date.description: The date entered by the user when this transaction occurred.

vendor_id.name: vendor_id
vendor_id.description: Reference to the vendor for this transaction.

_fivetran_deleted.description: Boolean created by Fivetran to indicate whether the record has been deleted.

source.quickbooks_source.quickbooks.acco.name: account
source.quickbooks_source.quickbooks.acco.description: Table containing components of a Chart Of Accounts and is part of a ledger. It is used to record a total monetary amount allocated against a specific use. Accounts are one of five basic types: asset, liability, revenue (income), expenses, or equity.

account_number.name: account_number
account_number.description: User-defined account number intended to identify the account within the Chart of Accounts.

sub_account.name: sub_account
sub_account.description: Specifies whether this object represents a parent (false) or a sub_account (true).

parent_account_id.name: parent_account_id
parent_account_id.description: User entered description for the account.

name.name: name
name.description: User recognizable name for the Account.

account_type.name: account_type
account_type.description: A detailed account classification that specifies the use of this account. The type is based on the Classification.

active.name: active
active.description: Boolean indicating whether an account is currently active.

account_sub_type.name: account_sub_type
account_sub_type.description: The account sub-type classification and is based on the AccountType value.

classification.name: classification
classification.description: The classification of an account. Not supported for non-posting accounts. Valid values include Asset, Equity, Expense, Liability, Revenue.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: Timestamp of the creation date for the account.

currency_id.name: currency_id
currency_id.description: Reference to the currency which the account records the balance in.

description.name: description
description.description: Description of the account.

balance.name: balance
balance.description: Specifies the balance amount for the current Account.

balance_with_sub_accounts.name: balance_with_sub_accounts
balance_with_sub_accounts.description: Specifies the balance amount for the current Account sub accounts.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: Timestamp of the date which the account was last updated.

city.name: city
city.description: The city which the address is located.

country.name: country
country.description: The country which the address is located.

line_1.name: line_1
line_1.description: The address_line_1 associated with the address.

line_2.name: line_2
line_2.description: The address_line_2 associated with the address (if applicable).

postal_code.name: postal_code
postal_code.description: The postal code which the address is located.

source.quickbooks_source.quickbooks.bill.description: Table containing distinct line items from bills within the `bill` table.

bill_id.name: bill_id
bill_id.description: Unique identifier of the parent bill record.

index.name: index
index.description: Bill line index in reference to the parent bill.

account_expense_class_id.name: account_expense_class_id
account_expense_class_id.description: Reference to the class associated with the account based expense bill line.

account_expense_customer_id.name: account_expense_customer_id
account_expense_customer_id.description: Reference to the customer associated with the account based expense bill line.

item_expense_item_id.name: item_expense_item_id
item_expense_item_id.description: Reference to the item with the item based expense bill line.

item_expense_class_id.description: Reference to the class associated with the item based expense bill line.

item_expense_customer_id.name: item_expense_customer_id
item_expense_customer_id.description: Reference to the customer associated with the item based expense bill line.

item_expense_billable_status.name: item_expense_billable_status
item_expense_billable_status.description: The billable status of the item based expense bill line.

account_expense_account_id.name: account_expense_account_id
account_expense_account_id.description: The identifier of the account associated with account being expensed from the bill.

account_expense_billable_status.name: account_expense_billable_status
account_expense_billable_status.description: The status of the bill line item expense.

account_expense_tax_code_id.name: account_expense_tax_code_id
account_expense_tax_code_id.description: The tax code id associated with the bill.

amount.name: amount
amount.description: Monetary amount of the bill line item.

description.name: description
description.description: Description of the bill line item.

macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__get_catalog.name: postgres__get_catalog
macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__get_catalog.macro_sql:
{% macro postgres__get_catalog(information_schema, schemas) -%}

  {%- call statement('catalog', fetch_result=True) -%}
    {#
      If the user has multiple databases set and the first one is wrong, this will fail.
      But we won't fail in the case where there are multiple quoting-difference-only dbs, which is better.
    #}
    {% set database = information_schema.database %}
    {{ adapter.verify_database(database) }}

    select
        '{{ database }}' as table_database,
        sch.nspname as table_schema,
        tbl.relname as table_name,
        case tbl.relkind
            when 'v' then 'VIEW'
            else 'BASE TABLE'
        end as table_type,
        tbl_desc.description as table_comment,
        col.attname as column_name,
        col.attnum as column_index,
        pg_catalog.format_type(col.atttypid, col.atttypmod) as column_type,
        col_desc.description as column_comment,
        pg_get_userbyid(tbl.relowner) as table_owner

    from pg_catalog.pg_namespace sch
    join pg_catalog.pg_class tbl on tbl.relnamespace = sch.oid
    join pg_catalog.pg_attribute col on col.attrelid = tbl.oid
    left outer join pg_catalog.pg_description tbl_desc on (tbl_desc.objoid = tbl.oid and tbl_desc.objsubid = 0)
    left outer join pg_catalog.pg_description col_desc on (col_desc.objoid = tbl.oid and col_desc.objsubid = col.attnum)

    where (
        {%- for schema in schemas -%}
          upper(sch.nspname) = upper('{{ schema }}'){%- if not loop.last %} or {% endif -%}
        {%- endfor -%}
      )
      and not pg_is_other_temp_schema(sch.oid) -- not a temporary schema belonging to another session
      and tbl.relpersistence in ('p', 'u') -- [p]ermanent table or [u]nlogged table. Exclude [t]emporary tables
      and tbl.relkind in ('r', 'v', 'f', 'p') -- o[r]dinary table, [v]iew, [f]oreign table, [p]artitioned table. Other values are [i]ndex, [S]equence, [c]omposite type, [t]OAST table, [m]aterialized view
      and col.attnum > 0 -- negative numbers are used for system columns such as oid
      and not col.attisdropped -- column as not been dropped

    order by
        sch.nspname,
        tbl.relname,
        col.attnum

  {%- endcall -%}

  {{ return(load_result('catalog').table) }}

{%- endmacro %}

macro.dbt_postgres.postgres_get_relation.name: postgres_get_relations
macro.dbt_postgres.postgres_get_relation.macro_sql:
{% macro postgres_get_relations () -%}

  {#
      -- in pg_depend, objid is the dependent, refobjid is the referenced object
      --  > a pg_depend entry indicates that the referenced object cannot be
      --  > dropped without also dropping the dependent object.
  #}

  {%- call statement('relations', fetch_result=True) -%}
    with relation as (
        select
            pg_rewrite.ev_class as class,
            pg_rewrite.oid as id
        from pg_rewrite
    ),
    class as (
        select
            oid as id,
            relname as name,
            relnamespace as schema,
            relkind as kind
        from pg_class
    ),
    dependency as (
        select distinct
            pg_depend.objid as id,
            pg_depend.refobjid as ref
        from pg_depend
    ),
    schema as (
        select
            pg_namespace.oid as id,
            pg_namespace.nspname as name
        from pg_namespace
        where nspname != 'information_schema' and nspname not like 'pg\_%'
    ),
    referenced as (
        select
            relation.id AS id,
            referenced_class.name ,
            referenced_class.schema ,
            referenced_class.kind
        from relation
        join class as referenced_class on relation.class=referenced_class.id
        where referenced_class.kind in ('r', 'v')
    ),
    relationships as (
        select
            referenced.name as referenced_name,
            referenced.schema as referenced_schema_id,
            dependent_class.name as dependent_name,
            dependent_class.schema as dependent_schema_id,
            referenced.kind as kind
        from referenced
        join dependency on referenced.id=dependency.id
        join class as dependent_class on dependency.ref=dependent_class.id
        where
            (referenced.name != dependent_class.name or
             referenced.schema != dependent_class.schema)
    )

    select
        referenced_schema.name as referenced_schema,
        relationships.referenced_name as referenced_name,
        dependent_schema.name as dependent_schema,
        relationships.dependent_name as dependent_name
    from relationships
    join schema as dependent_schema on relationships.dependent_schema_id=dependent_schema.id
    join schema as referenced_schema on relationships.referenced_schema_id=referenced_schema.id
    group by referenced_schema, referenced_name, dependent_schema, dependent_name
    order by referenced_schema, referenced_name, dependent_schema, dependent_name;

  {%- endcall -%}

  {{ return(load_result('relations').table) }}
{% endmacro %}

    select

      tablename as name,
      schemaname as schema,
      'table' as type
    from pg_tables
    where schemaname ilike '{{ schema_relation.schema }}'
    union all

    where schemaname ilike '{{ schema_relation.schema }}'

macro.dbt.default__snapshot_merge_sql.name: default__snapshot_merge_sql
macro.dbt.default__snapshot_merge_sql.macro_sql:
{% macro default__snapshot_merge_sql(target, source, insert_cols) -%}
    {%- set insert_cols_csv = insert_cols | join(', ') -%}

    merge into {{ target }} as DBT_INTERNAL_DEST
    using {{ source }} as DBT_INTERNAL_SOURCE
    on DBT_INTERNAL_SOURCE.dbt_scd_id = DBT_INTERNAL_DEST.dbt_scd_id

    when matched
     and DBT_INTERNAL_DEST.dbt_valid_to is null
     and DBT_INTERNAL_SOURCE.dbt_change_type in ('update', 'delete')
        then update
        set dbt_valid_to = DBT_INTERNAL_SOURCE.dbt_valid_to

    when not matched
     and DBT_INTERNAL_SOURCE.dbt_change_type = 'insert'
        then insert ({{ insert_cols_csv }})
        values ({{ insert_cols_csv }})

{% endmacro %}

macro.dbt.default__snapshot_staging_tabl.macro_sql:
{% macro default__snapshot_staging_table(strategy, source_sql, target_relation) -%}

    with snapshot_query as (

        {{ source_sql }}

    ),

    snapshotted_data as (

        select *,
            {{ strategy.unique_key }} as dbt_unique_key

        from {{ target_relation }}
        where dbt_valid_to is null

    ),

    insertions_source_data as (

        select
            *,
            {{ strategy.unique_key }} as dbt_unique_key,
            {{ strategy.updated_at }} as dbt_updated_at,
            {{ strategy.updated_at }} as dbt_valid_from,
            nullif({{ strategy.updated_at }}, {{ strategy.updated_at }}) as dbt_valid_to,
            {{ strategy.scd_id }} as dbt_scd_id

        from snapshot_query
    ),

    updates_source_data as (

        select
            *,
            {{ strategy.unique_key }} as dbt_unique_key,
            {{ strategy.updated_at }} as dbt_updated_at,
            {{ strategy.updated_at }} as dbt_valid_from,
            {{ strategy.updated_at }} as dbt_valid_to

        from snapshot_query
    ),

    {%- if strategy.invalidate_hard_deletes %}

    deletes_source_data as (

        select
            *,
            {{ strategy.unique_key }} as dbt_unique_key
        from snapshot_query
    ),
    {% endif %}

    insertions as (

        select
            'insert' as dbt_change_type,
            source_data.*

        from insertions_source_data as source_data
        left outer join snapshotted_data on snapshotted_data.dbt_unique_key = source_data.dbt_unique_key
        where snapshotted_data.dbt_unique_key is null
           or (
                snapshotted_data.dbt_unique_key is not null
            and (
                {{ strategy.row_changed }}
            )
        )

    ),

    updates as (

        select
            'update' as dbt_change_type,
            source_data.*,
            snapshotted_data.dbt_scd_id

        from updates_source_data as source_data
        join snapshotted_data on snapshotted_data.dbt_unique_key = source_data.dbt_unique_key
        where (
            {{ strategy.row_changed }}
        )
    )

    {%- if strategy.invalidate_hard_deletes -%}
    ,

    deletes as (

        select
            'delete' as dbt_change_type,
            source_data.*,
            {{ snapshot_get_time() }} as dbt_valid_from,
            {{ snapshot_get_time() }} as dbt_updated_at,
            {{ snapshot_get_time() }} as dbt_valid_to,
            snapshotted_data.dbt_scd_id

        from snapshotted_data
        left join deletes_source_data as source_data on snapshotted_data.dbt_unique_key = source_data.dbt_unique_key
        where source_data.dbt_unique_key is null
    )
    {%- endif %}

    select * from insertions
    union all
    select * from updates
    {%- if strategy.invalidate_hard_deletes %}
    union all
    select * from deletes
    {%- endif %}

{%- endmacro %}

dbt.__overview__.name: __overview__
dbt.__overview__.block_contents:
### Welcome!

Welcome to the auto-generated documentation for your dbt project!

### Navigation

You can use the `Project` and `Database` navigation tabs on the left side of the window to explore the models
in your project.

#### Project Tab
The `Project` tab mirrors the directory structure of your dbt project. In this tab, you can see all of the
models defined in your dbt project, as well as models imported from dbt packages.

#### Database Tab
The `Database` tab also exposes your models, but in a format that looks more like a database explorer. This view
shows relations (tables and views) grouped into database schemas. Note that ephemeral models are _not_ shown
in this interface, as they do not exist in the database.

### Graph Exploration
You can click the blue icon on the bottom-right corner of the page to view the lineage graph of your models.

On model pages, you'll see the immediate parents and children of the model you're exploring. By clicking the `Expand`
button at the top-right of this lineage pane, you'll be able to see all of the models that are used to build,
or are built from, the model you're exploring.

Once expanded, you'll be able to use the `--select` and `--exclude` model selection syntax to filter the
models in the graph. For more information on model selection, check out the [dbt docs](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/model-selection-syntax).

Note that you can also right-click on models to interactively filter and explore the graph.

---

### More information

- [What is dbt](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/introduction)?
- Read the [dbt viewpoint](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/viewpoint)
- [Installation](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/installation)
- Join the [dbt Community](https://www.getdbt.com/community/) for questions and discussion

quickbooks_source.account_table.name: account_table
quickbooks_source.account_table.block_contents: Table containing components of a Chart Of Accounts and is part of a ledger. It is used to record a total monetary amount allocated against a specific use. Accounts are one of five basic types: asset, liability, revenue (income), expenses, or equity.

quickbooks_source.bill_line_table.name: bill_line_table
quickbooks_source.bill_line_table.block_contents: Table containing distinct line items from bills within the `bill` table.

quickbooks_source.bill_linked_txn_table.name: bill_linked_txn_table
quickbooks_source.bill_linked_txn_table.block_contents: Mapping table containing bill payment transactions linked to a bill.

quickbooks_source.bill_payment_line_tabl.name: bill_payment_line_table
quickbooks_source.bill_payment_line_tabl.block_contents: Table containing individual line items of a bill payment, which are recorded within the `bill_payment` table.

quickbooks_source.bill_payment_table.name: bill_payment_table
quickbooks_source.bill_payment_table.block_contents: Table containing payment transactions bills that the business owner receives from a vendor for goods or services purchased from the vendor.

quickbooks_source.bill_table.name: bill_table
quickbooks_source.bill_table.block_contents: Table containing AP transactions representing a request-for-payment from a third party for goods/services rendered, received, or both.

quickbooks_source.bundle_item_table.name: bundle_item_table
quickbooks_source.bundle_item_table.block_contents: Mapping table containing all bundle and item combinations.

quickbooks_source.bundle_table.name: bundle_table
quickbooks_source.bundle_table.block_contents: Table containing all bundles possible to be used within an invoice.

quickbooks_source.credit_card_payment_tx.name: credit_card_payment_txn_table
quickbooks_source.credit_card_payment_tx.block_contents: Table containing all credit card payment transactions.

quickbooks_source.credit_memo_line_table.name: credit_memo_line_table
quickbooks_source.credit_memo_line_table.block_contents: Table containing individual records of credit memos.

quickbooks_source.credit_memo_table.name: credit_memo_table
quickbooks_source.credit_memo_table.block_contents: Table containing credit memo records. A credit memo is a refund or credit of payment or part of a payment for goods or services that have been sold.

quickbooks_source.customer_table.name: customer_table
quickbooks_source.customer_table.block_contents: Table containing customers of which are consumers of the service or product that your business offers.

quickbooks_source.department_table.name: department_table
quickbooks_source.department_table.block_contents: Table containing records representing physical locations such as stores, and sales regions.

quickbooks_source.deposit_line_table.name: deposit_line_table
quickbooks_source.deposit_line_table.block_contents: Table containing individual line items comprising the deposit.

quickbooks_source.deposit_table.name: deposit_table
quickbooks_source.deposit_table.block_contents: Table containing records of transactions that record on or more deposits of a customer payment or a new direct deposit.

quickbooks_source.estimate_line_table.name: estimate_line_table
quickbooks_source.estimate_line_table.block_contents: Table containing line item records of an estimate.

quickbooks_source.estimate_table.name: estimate_table
quickbooks_source.estimate_table.block_contents: Table containing estimates. An estimate represents a proposal for a financial transaction from a business to a customer for goods or services proposed to be sold, including proposed pricing.

quickbooks_source.invoice_line_bundle_ta.name: invoice_line_bundle_table
quickbooks_source.invoice_line_bundle_ta.block_contents: Table containing lines of an invoice which were bundled.

quickbooks_source.invoice_line_table.name: invoice_line_table
quickbooks_source.invoice_line_table.block_contents: Table containing individual records from invoices.

quickbooks_source.invoice_linked_txn_tab.name: invoice_linked_txn_table
quickbooks_source.invoice_linked_txn_tab.block_contents: Mapping table for invoices records to respective estimate and payment objects.

quickbooks_source.invoice_table.name: invoice_table
quickbooks_source.invoice_table.block_contents: Table containing invoice records. An Invoice represents a sales form where the customer pays for a product or service later.

quickbooks_source.item_table.name: item_table
quickbooks_source.item_table.block_contents: Table containing item records. An item is a thing that your company buys, sells, or re-sells, such as products and services.

quickbooks_source.journal_entry_line_tab.name: journal_entry_line_table
quickbooks_source.journal_entry_line_tab.block_contents: Table containing individual line items of a transaction associated with a journal entry.

quickbooks_source.payment_line_table.name: payment_line_table
quickbooks_source.payment_line_table.block_contents: Table containing individual line items recorded within a payment.

quickbooks_source.payment_table.name: payment_table
quickbooks_source.payment_table.block_contents: Table containing all payment records. The payment can be applied for a particular customer against multiple Invoices and Credit Memos. It can also be created without any Invoice or Credit Memo, by just specifying an amount.

quickbooks_source.purchase_line_table.name: purchase_line_table
quickbooks_source.purchase_line_table.block_contents: Table containing individual line items of a transaction associated with a purchase.

quickbooks_source.purchase_order_line_ta.name: purchase_order_line_table
quickbooks_source.purchase_order_line_ta.block_contents: Table containing individual line items of a transaction associated with a purchase order.

quickbooks_source.purchase_order_linked_.name: purchase_order_linked_txn_table
quickbooks_source.purchase_order_linked_.block_contents: Mapping table for purchase order records to respective bill and purchase objects.

quickbooks_source.purchase_order_table.name: purchase_order_table
quickbooks_source.purchase_order_table.block_contents: Table containing records of purchase orders (PO).

quickbooks_source.purchase_table.name: purchase_table
quickbooks_source.purchase_table.block_contents: Table containing records of purchase expenses.

quickbooks_source.refund_receipt_line_ta.name: refund_receipt_line_table
quickbooks_source.refund_receipt_line_ta.block_contents: Table containing individual line items of a refund transaction.

quickbooks_source.refund_receipt_table.name: refund_receipt_table
quickbooks_source.refund_receipt_table.block_contents: Table containing refunds to the customer for a product or service that was provided.

quickbooks_source.sales_receipt_line_tab.name: sales_receipt_line_table
quickbooks_source.sales_receipt_line_tab.block_contents: Table containing individual line items of a sales transaction.

quickbooks_source.sales_receipt_table.name: sales_receipt_table
quickbooks_source.sales_receipt_table.block_contents: Table containing sales receipts that are given to a customer. A sales receipt, payment is received as part of the sale of goods and services. The sales receipt specifies a deposit account where the customer's payment is deposited.

quickbooks_source.transfer_table.name: transfer_table
quickbooks_source.transfer_table.block_contents: Table containing records of transfers. A Transfer represents a transaction where funds are moved between two accounts from the company's QuickBooks chart of accounts.

quickbooks_source.vendor_credit_line_tab.name: vendor_credit_line_table
quickbooks_source.vendor_credit_line_tab.block_contents: Table containing individual vendor credit line items.

quickbooks_source.vendor_credit_table.name: vendor_credit_table
quickbooks_source.vendor_credit_table.block_contents: Table containing all vendor credit records. A vendor credit is an accounts payable transaction that represents a refund or credit of payment for goods or services.

quickbooks_source.vendor_table.name: vendor_table
quickbooks_source.vendor_table.block_contents: Table containing all vendor records. A vendor is the seller from whom your company purchases any service or product.

quickbooks_source.account_id.name: account_id
quickbooks_source.account_id.block_contents: The identifier of the account associated

quickbooks_source._fivetran_deleted.name: _fivetran_deleted
quickbooks_source._fivetran_deleted.block_contents: Boolean created by Fivetran to indicate whether the record has been deleted.
